ps, the Germans may have been the largest.Aaron Spencer Fogleman has written the first comprehensive history of this eighteenth-century German settlement of North America. Utilizing a vast body of published and archival sources, many of them never before made accessible outside of Germany, Fogleman emphasizes the importance of German immigration to colonial America, the European context of the Germans' emigration, and the importance of networks to their success in America  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Nov 2019) 0aGerman AmericansxHistoryy18th century. 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesxHistoryy18th century. 4aAmerican History. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aBooks of Regional Interest. 7aHISTORY / United States / Colonial Period (1600-1775).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn eBook Package Archive 1898-1999 (pre Pub)z978311044252640uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/9780812291674423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780812291674.jpg  a978-3-11-044252-6  Penn eBook Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA10PENN  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG